---
description: "Deployment Frequency Developer Workflow"
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
---
description: "Execute GitHub workflow with Jira integration"
inputs:
  developer: "{{developer}}"  # Developer assigned to the task
  usecase: "{{usecase}}"     # Feature being developed (e.g., "Add Login", "User Dashboard", "Payment Integration")
  requirements: "{{requirements}}" # Detailed requirements for code generation

steps:
  1. Create Jira issue (create-jira-issue.mdc) -> outputs issue_key
  2. Generate API and Query Specs
     - Build API spec (build-api-template.mdc -> api-spec.mdc)
     - Build Elastic query (build-elastic-query.mdc -> elastic-query.mdc)
  3. Generate Code
     - Generate all layers (generate-code.mdc)
     - Validate generated code
  4. Create Git branch (create-git-branch.mdc) # Branch will be created as AIA-{issue_key}
  5. Add and commit generated code (commit-code.mdc)
  6. Push changes (push-branch.mdc)
  7. Create pull request (create-pr.mdc)
  8. Add Jira comment (add-jira-comment.mdc)
  9. Transition Jira issue (transition-jira-issue.mdc)

validation:
  # Validate requirements format
  - validate requirements --format
  # Validate generated code
  - validate code --all
  # Check if all files are committed
  - validate git --status

